---
const updated = "October 3, 2025";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Refund Policy | Knit by Machine</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --kbm-green: #52682d;
        --kbm-green-2: #738c52;
        --page-bg: #f7f8f7;
      }
      body {
        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial;
        line-height: 1.65;
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--page-bg);
        color: #1f2937;
      }
      main {
        max-width: 860px;
        padding: 80px 20px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .kbm-breadcrumb {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: #6b7280;
      }
      .kbm-legal h1 {
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.4rem);
        line-height: 1.2;
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
      }
      .meta {
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      .kbm-card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 24px 22px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
      }
      .kbm-toc {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 14px 16px;
        margin: 0 0 24px 0;
      }
      .kbm-toc details summary {
        cursor: pointer;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .kbm-toc nav a {
        display: block;
        padding: 6px 0;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--kbm-green);
      }
      .kbm-toc nav a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      /* Back-to-top button */
      #kbm-top {
        position: fixed;
        bottom: 30px;
        right: 30px;
        width: 46px;
        height: 46px;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--kbm-green);
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        cursor: pointer;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
        opacity: 0;
        visibility: hidden;
        transition: opacity 0.3s ease, visibility 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
        z-index: 9999;
      }
      #kbm-top.show {
        opacity: 1;
        visibility: visible;
      }
      #kbm-top:hover {
        background: var(--kbm-green-2);
        transform: translateY(-3px);
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main>
      <div class="kbm-legal">
        <div class="kbm-breadcrumb">Knit by Machine ▸ Refund Policy</div>
        <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
        <div class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</div>

        <aside class="kbm-toc">
          <details open>
            <summary>On this page</summary>
            <nav>
              <a href="#general">1. General Policy</a>
              <a href="#memberships">2. Memberships</a>
              <a href="#digital-products">3. Courses, Patterns, and Digital Products</a>
              <a href="#workshops">4. Workshops or Events</a>
              <a href="#exceptions">5. Exceptions</a>
              <a href="#contact">6. Contact Us</a>
            </nav>
          </details>
        </aside>

        <section class="kbm-card">
          <h2 id="general">1. General Policy</h2>
          <p>At Knit by Machine, we want you to be satisfied with your purchase. Because our products and memberships provide immediate access to digital content, refunds are limited.</p>

          <h2 id="memberships">2. Memberships</h2>
          <p>All membership purchases are billed in advance and are non-refundable once access is granted. You may cancel your membership at any time, and your access will continue through the end of your billing period.</p>

          <h2 id="digital-products">3. Courses, Patterns, and Digital Products</h2>
          <p>Due to the nature of digital content, refunds are generally not offered once a course, pattern, or download has been accessed. If you experience issues accessing your purchase, please contact us and we will work to resolve the problem.</p>

          <h2 id="workshops">4. Workshops or Events</h2>
          <p>If you register for a live workshop or event and cannot attend, please notify us as soon as possible. We may, at our discretion, provide access to a replay or apply your payment toward a future workshop.</p>

          <h2 id="exceptions">5. Exceptions</h2>
          <p>We may consider refund requests in special cases, such as duplicate purchases or technical problems that prevent access. These requests must be submitted within 7 days of purchase.</p>

          <h2 id="contact">6. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have questions about this policy or need assistance with a purchase, please contact us at:</p>
          <p><a href="mailto:contact@KnitbyMachine.com">contact@KnitbyMachine.com</a></p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <button id="kbm-top" aria-label="Back to top">↑</button>

      <script>
        const topBtn = document.getElementById("kbm-top");
        window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
          if (window.scrollY > 200) topBtn.classList.add("show");
          else topBtn.classList.remove("show");
        });
        topBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
          window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: "smooth" });
        });
      </script>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
